article.headline: Youngstown State defeats Warren Wilson 104-58
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Bobby Hain scored 18 points and grabbed 13 rebounds as Youngstown State defeated Division II Warren Wilson 104-58 Thursday night. Hain was 7 of 11 from the floor and 4 of 6 from the line while playing 22 minutes. Youngstown State (4-0) shot 73.5 percent after halftime, netting 62 points. Three other Penguins scored in double-figures. Kendrick Perry hit four 3-pointers and also had a game-high 18 points. Kamren Belin had 17 points while Shawn Amiker added 12. The 104 points is the most for Youngstown State since scoring 106 against Slippery Rock in 2003. The Penguins have won three games in three days and are off to their best start since 2000-01. Warren Wilson (2-6) made their first four field goals and led the Penguins 10-9 with 17:38 remaining in the first half. Justin Gonyea had a team-high 14 points for the Owls.
